  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Grate your<strong> cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Drain your <strong>tuna</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1697645655396-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1697645655396-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1697645655396-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1697645655396-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1697645655396-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>farfalle</strong> to a pot of boiled water with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>farfalle</strong> for 6-7 min</p><p>Tip: It doesn't need to be fully cooked, as it will go in the oven later!</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>farfalle</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1697645659406-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1697645659406-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1697645659406-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1697645659406-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1697645659406-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the pasta is cooking, melt 20g <span class=\"text-purple\">[30g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[40g]</span><strong> butter</strong> in a pot over a medium heat</p><p>Once melted, add 20g <span class=\"text-purple\">[30g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[40g]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms – this is your <strong>roux</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1697645664002-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1697645664002-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1697645664002-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1697645664002-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1697645664002-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Gradually whisk 250ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [375ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> into the roux, a little at a time, and cook for 5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains – this is your <strong>béchamel sauce</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and<strong> half </strong>the <strong>grated cheese </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)<strong> </strong>to the béchamel sauce and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>cheese sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1697645668009-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1697645668009-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1697645668009-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1697645668009-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1697645668009-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove the pot from the heat and stir your <strong>garden veg mix</strong> and <strong>drained farfalle</strong> through the<strong> cheese sauce</strong> with the <strong>drained tuna </strong>and 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml] </span><strong>reserved starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>tuna pasta mix</strong></p><p>Transfer the<strong> tuna pasta mix </strong>to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1697645672066-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1697645672066-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1697645672066-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1697645672066-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1697645672066-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> panko breadcrumbs</strong> and <strong>remaining grated cheese</strong> to a small bowl with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>cheesy crunchy topping</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1697645675277-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1697645675277-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1697645675277-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1697645675277-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1697645675277-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top the tuna pasta mix evenly with the <strong>cheesy crunchy topping</strong></p><p>Put the dish in the oven for 10-12 min or until golden and bubbling – this is your<strong> creamy tuna pasta bake</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1697645679453-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1697645679453-x400.jpg",
